  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (inconsistent requirements variant)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Two acceptance requirements are bound to the hemolysis claim; one specifies RH < 1.0 as the passing threshold for all operating points, while the other mandates RH ≤ 1.05 as the minimum permissible bound and explicitly prohibits acceptance of any result below RH = 1.0 on the grounds that sub-unity values indicate measurement artefact. These requirements are mutually exclusive: the first forbids RH ≥ 1.0, the second forbids RH < 1.0.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/cpb-hemolysis-rh-primary",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cpb-hemolysis-worst-case",
